% Installing

gcc‑lua‑cdecl may be installed using [LuaRocks] or [Git].

Before installing the module, make sure to [install the Lua plugin for
GCC][Installing gcc‑lua].

[LuaRocks]: http://luarocks.org/
[Git]: http://git-scm.com/
[Installing gcc‑lua]: http://colberg.org/gcc-lua/INSTALL.html


Using LuaRocks
--------------

Install the module in your home directory:

~~~
luarocks install --local gcc-lua-cdecl
~~~

Verify that the module has been installed:

~~~
luarocks list gcc-lua-cdecl
~~~

To use the module, set the Lua module path:

~~~
eval `luarocks path`
~~~

The command can be added to the shell’s startup file, e.g., `~/.bashrc`.


Using Git
---------

Obtain the source from the [git repository]:

~~~
git clone http://git.colberg.org/gcc-lua-cdecl
~~~

In the repository, checkout the latest release version:

~~~
git checkout 1.2.0
~~~

If you have GnuPG, verify that the tag is signed by the following key:

~~~
git tag -v 1.2.0
~~~

~~~
Primary key fingerprint: 2997 6EC2 2BD1 EBBC CC77  F3A6 183B D5ED 3527 8611
     Subkey fingerprint: 983B F9D0 F02A 6014 0CEC  529F 767E 12A8 C92A 31CB
~~~

The module is accompanied by a test suite:

~~~
make test
~~~

By default, the tests assume that the gcc‑lua and gcc‑lua‑cdecl repositories are
located in the same parent directory. If the gcc‑lua plugin is installed in the
[GCC plugin directory][GCC Loading Plugins] instead, override the make variable
`GCCLUA`:

~~~
make test GCCLUA=gcclua
~~~

[git repository]: http://git.colberg.org/gcc-lua-cdecl
[GCC Loading Plugins]: http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gccint/Plugins-loading.html
